The Neshoba County School District is proud to announce that Mrs. Becky Spears has been named the recipient of the the Javits/Frasier Scholarship. As a member of the Javits-Frasier Scholars, she will receive complimentary registration to the National Association of Gifted Children 67th Annual Convention. The purpose of this scholarship is to increase culturally and linguistically diverse students‚Äô access to talent development opportunities through educator training and support related to equity and excellence in gifted education.
Congratulations Mrs. Spears!

post_text:
Congratulations to our students and staff on an outstanding first week of school!

Car Rider Line- We know the line is very long at this time. In an attempt to possibly alleviate congestion, if you have an NCMS and NCHS student to drop off, please take St. Francis Dr. from the hospital to enter the middle/high school line if at all possible.

Outstanding job by our staff and students on our new safety protocols! Let's stay healthy!

Reminder- If you are under quarantine, awaiting Covid test results, or have tested positive, please contact the school to let them know. DO NOT COME TO SCHOOL if you or your family is under quarantine. Please remember, if you come to school under these circumstances you will be sent to alternative school or possibly expelled. The safety and health of our staff and students is paramount.

On Monday, August 10, a technology survey will be sent home to each student. These should be returned by Wednesday, August 12.

#OneCommunity #OneMission #OneNeshoba

PARENTS of ELEMENTARY STUDENTS:
üî¥We understand that this year we may have many more car riders than we have had in the past. We ask that if your child will be a car rider every day, you send a note to the teacher on the first day of school that states - child‚Äôs name, date and permanent car rider.
üî¥If you must make changes to your child‚Äôs daily transportation, you will need to send the child‚Äôs teacher a note each day of the change.
üî¥If you are changing buses permanently, you must contact our transportation director. Any bus change note for that day must include: student‚Äôs name, parent‚Äôs name, phone number, bus # and the address where the child will be dropped off. Bus change notes will only be taken for one week and then a permanent change must be completed.
üî¥If you wish to change from a car rider back to your permanently assigned bus, the teacher needs a note with the that information on the day of the change.

post_text: NCHS welcomes Russell Cruise to the Rocket Nation! Russell will serve as NCHS Head Boys Basketball Coach/Assistant Girls Basketball Coach/Assistant Track for the upcoming school year. post_text:
FORMER ROCKET SPOTLIGHT
Jamie Carter is a graduate of Neshoba Central High School where he played football for the Rockets. Coach Carter has been named the Head Football Coach at Osceola High School in Arkansas.
Coach Carter spent two seasons as defensive coordinator at Class 6A Marion High School. Prior to coaching the Patriots, Carter spent two seasons at Saginaw High School in Texas. Coach Carter also has experience coaching at high schools in Alabama and Georgia, and three seasons at Faulkner University in Montgomery, Alabama.
A native of Philadelphia, Mississippi, Coach Carter attended and played football at the University of Alabama. He played defensive line for the Crimson Tide and was a member of the 1998 Tide team which lost the Orange Bowl to Michigan.
Carter spent two seasons in the National Football League with the New York Giants and the Dallas Cowboys.
#weareproudofyou #formerrocket #onecommunity #onemission #oneneshoba
Lundy Brantley Dareyl Carter

Important Information:

‚Ä¢ The NCSD is continuing to offer educational opportunities until the end of the semester in May.
‚Ä¢ Report cards will be issued at the normal time when school is out in May.
‚Ä¢ Grades for the year will be as follows: 1st Semester- 67% 2nd Semester- 33%
Example 1‚Ä¶1st semester average is 80 and 3rd 9-weeks grade is 95.
80 x .67 = 53.6
95 x .33 = 31.35
53.6 + 31.35 = 84.95 or 85
Example 2‚Ä¶1st semester average is 63 and 3rd 9 weeks is 72.
63 x .67 = 42.21
72 x .33 = 23.76
42.21 + 23.76 = 65.97 or 66
Classes at NCHS and NCMS that meet for one (1) semester, the 3rd 9-week grade will also be the final grade.
‚Ä¢ Dual Credit classes are calculated as normal.
‚Ä¢ If you have questions about this process and/or your child‚Äôs progress, please email the principal of the school your child attends.
#OneCommunity #OneMission #OneNeshoba

GENERAL MUSIC ASSIGNMENTS
This assignment is for the weeks of 20-24 and April 27-May 1

I. Watch the following video on the Renaissance Musical Period, and answer the following questions.
https://youtu.be/z5I6qi9qwRg

1. What are the dates of the Renaissance Period?
2. Name an English composer of Renaissance music.
3. Which Renaissance composer was given the exclusive license to print music in England?
4. How did the invention of Johannes Gutenburg‚Äôs printing press help in the realm of music (3)?
5. Name a composer who moved to Mexico and developed hybrid Spanish/Mexican music.
6. What is a Pavane?
7. Which instruments played in a Quarante?
8. What is a madrigal?
9. Name 4 instruments of the Renaissance period.

II. Listen to the following video and describe the madrigal arrangement of Dark Horse in a well formed paragraph.

https://youtu.be/hPZTT0ZYhS4

Please submit assignments to your respective teacher.
Amay@neshobacentral.com Awade@neshobacentral.com rboykin@neshobacentral.com
